Parents’ role of inculcating proper moral and ethical behaviour in their children cannot be gainsaidParents cannot shirk from their responsibilities and dump children in school for teachers to mould into responsible citizens. The ‘work-from-home’ directive meant to curb the spread of Covid-19 brought an uneasy closeness between family members who had virtually been living apart due to modern lifestyles.
 It has been pointed out that the change from the traditional unit, where families spend most of their time together, to the modern lifestyle, where children attend boarding school and parents work in towns, has resulted in disjointed relationships.



